  "texts": [
    "We use the root mean square error (rmse) in the predicted angles to evaluate the surface normals task.",
    "We also measure the overall performance ∆m as the average per-task reduc-tion in performance compared to the single-task baseline st:∆m = 1 T T i=1 (-1) li (M i -M st,i)/M st,i(3)where l i = 1 if a lower value means better for performance measure M i of task i, and 0 otherwise.",
    "The single-task performance is measured for a fully converged model that uses the same backbone network only for that task.",
    "Implementation: MTLoRA is implemented using PyTorch, and the code is publicly available on GitHub.",
    "Our main artifact is an easily pluggable MTLoRALinear layer that encapsulates our TS-LoRA and TA-LoRA modules, enabling the model to adapt to different tasks by using task-specific lowrank matrices."
